All variable name, class name and method name should be self-descriptive.
All major methods, classes and files have to have explanation of what it does.

Variable: 
name: First word of the variable name will be in uppercase. Following words’ first letter will be in uppercase and remaining letters will be in lowercase.
Local Variable : It must be unique within the same scope  
Class name: Name will be unique and the first character of the class name will be uppercase , e.g (Map)
Method name: each keyword before arguments starts with lower case character with each consecutive words first letter capitalized.
Eg(bool isEmpty(Map&[]) ) ;

Code formats:
All methods requires a whitespace at the end.
All codes should be properly indented.
All setter methods should start with the word “set”.
All getter methods should start with the word “get”.
